article.headline: Fla Atlantic 95, Campbell 90
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- Quinton Young scored 20 points to lead Florida Atlantic to a 95-90 victory over Campbell Thursday. Florida Atlantic (10-10, 9-4) ended the first half with a slight lead over Campbell (8-13,7-7) with 48-46. Florida Atlantic then outscored Campbell 47-44 in the second half. Only a point behind Young for Florida Atlantic was Carlos Monroe with 19. Rodney Webb scored 16, Kevin Green scored 13 and DeAndre Rice scored 10. Campbell's Eric Smith was the high scorer for the game with 31 points. Maurice Latham scored 17 points for the team, along with grabbing 10 rebounds, and Ledell Eackles scored another 14.
